org.codethechange.culturemesh.models

Class Network

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.codethechange.culturemesh.models.Network
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, Postable

    public class Network
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable, Postable
    This class stores all the information related to a network. It is fully expanded, meaning that its instance fields like nearLocation store expanded objects (i.e. Place, not the stripped-down forms for database storage.
    See Also:

      • toJSON

        public org.json.JSONObject toJSON()
                           throws org.json.JSONException
        Generate a JSON describing the object. The JSON will conform to the following format: 
             
         {
                  "id_city_cur": 0,
                  "city_cur": "string",
                  "id_region_cur": 0,
                  "region_cur": "string",
                  "id_country_cur": 0,
                  "country_cur": "string",
                  "id_city_origin": 0,
                  "city_origin": "string",
                  "id_region_origin": 0,
                  "region_origin": "string",
                  "id_country_origin": 0,
                  "country_origin": "string",
                  "id_language_origin": 0,
                  "language_origin": "string",
                  "network_class": "string"
               }
        where missing IDs are passed as Location.NOWHERE. This format is suitable for submission to the server using the /network/new POST endpoint.
        Returns:
        JSON representation of the object
        Throws:
        org.json.JSONException - Unclear when this would be thrown
